DFT. I almost took a gain, but the stock is a keeper.

DLR vs DFT.
DLR Price/FFO is $31.6/($2.75 to $2.90) = 11
DFT Price/FFO is $5.0/($0.96 to $1.12) = 5

Note that yahoo earnings estimates are generally FFO for reits, and for DLR
they are, but for DFT yahoo uses EPS in error.

DFT AFFO was 81 cents in 2008. At least it would have covered the 75 dividend
run rate.

I think FFO is a good measure of profitability. Data Center leases have cost
increases built in while the facilities are already built. Yes, they have to
maintain them and upgrade as needed, but as they say...

"Core cooling and power infrastructure, which accounts for the majority of
buildoutcosts, has minimal risk of obsolescence."

"HVAC and power technologies have not materially changed for decades. Long
useful lives of 30+ years."

When things get less frightening, DFT will reinstate the 75 cent annual
dividend. 75/500 = 15%. maybe in 2010?

They went public in 2007 at $21. EV/EBITDA = 9.4 And NBV is $15+ a share, or
300% of stock price. And these assets are not distressed or idle. They are
worth full book value.

