Date:2/21/2009 11:08:09 AM
From:MCsweet
Anializer,

In general, I also do not trust companies that use pro-forma accounting
numbers. However, I think you are double counting. The losses consist of
goodwill writedowns and intangible amortization plus losses on the ARPs. Since
these balance sheet items are approaching 0 anyway, those losses will not
continue to eat into book value. More importantly, you have already subtracted
them out of tangible book, so saying they will eat into tangible book value is
not correct IMO.

That's why I recommend you look at the cash flows.

I agree it is correct to mark the intangibles to 0. So you have 0.55 in book
plus significant positive operating cash flows, plus potential for an ARPs
settlement in cash equal to the current value of the stock price. Plus a
buyback of another $1 million or so coming up.

MC
